text:
Intro:
feeling that diesel, you know i'm ready,
i'm ricky rock'n'rollin', going steady,

Verse 1:
better prepare an obit for the haters,
love the sound of their tears in the gale's respirator.
my girl, she always tryna keep me locked in,
but all i really need is just the two of us, so let's begin.
check it out yo, watch me do my thing,
i'm ricky the rock 'n' roller, no one can bring me down, king.
ricky the rock 'n' roller got the crowd screaming for more,
turn it up some more, they'll be begging for encore.

Pre-Chorus:
they know how it goes, they seen the pain
so why do you cry, listen to my refrain.

Chorus:
check out this feeling, it's pure satisfaction,
i ride that rolls, ain't no lookin' back in my action.
i can't get her off my mind, this girl's got a hold on me,
but i wouldn't have it any other way, she sets me free.

Verse 2:
ain't nothin' but a game, dealing with this pain,
but we gotta move them biscuits, gotta stay in the flame,
love is always welcome, but it's never the same.
better grab a pen and paper, take some notes,
these niggas, they with me, we out here making dope,
and you just see right through me, no need to be sneaky,
let's get sleazy, baby, ain't no need to be neat- y.
let the rhythm guide us, let it take command,

Pre-Chorus:
when you died, my heart stopped beating
now i'm ready to go, my soul is fleeting.

Chorus:
toting up in miami, livin' it large,
you give me bad bad love and it's leaving me scarred,
but we are not just another hollywood facade.
let the music take control, let it lift you higher,

Bridge:
we the bomb and we 'bout to explode,
got rodan on your mind, we got you in that mode.
we are what we are, we keep it real, unglued
that's just how it is, we call it screwed.

Outro:
if i can't work my magic, what's the point in tryin'?
i'm taking off, now see, no denying.

Instrumental:
blow it in your face, stacking up these benjis
nothing you say can stop me, tryna get this oprah money with ease.

active_struct.name: The Dynamic Duo
attrs: has a unique structure with two prechoruses before the first chorus
utilizes a double chorus after the second verse for a bigger impact
includes an instrumental section after the bridge for a break from vocals
ends with a final chorus and a strong outro to wrap up the song neatly

struct_suggs.name: The Emotional Rollercoaster
attrs: has a catchy intro that sets the tone for the song
follows a traditional verse-chorus structure, making it easy to follow along
includes an instrumental section for added interest and variation
ends with a strong outro, leaving a lasting impression on the listener

struct_suggs.name: The Bridge Builder
attrs: has a unique prechorus before the first chorus, adding more depth to the song
includes a bridge for a change in pace and mood
utilizes an instrumental section after the bridge, allowing for a break from vocals
ends with a final chorus and a strong outro to tie the song together

struct_suggs.name: The Introvert's Journey
attrs: has an intricate intro that sets up the musical themes for the rest of the song
includes an instrumental interlude after the first chorus for added interest and variation
has a prechorus before the second chorus to build up to a bigger climax
ends with a final chorus and a powerful outro to leave a lasting impact on the listener

struct_suggs.name: The Chorus Queen
attrs: has multiple prechorus and chorus repetitions, making it suitable for a longer song
includes a bridge and instrumental section for added variety and interest
has a distinct build up to the final chorus in the outro
maintains a strong structure and flow despite multiple repetitions of certain parts

struct_suggs.name: The Dynamic Duo
attrs: has a unique structure with two prechoruses before the first chorus
utilizes a double chorus after the second verse for a bigger impact
includes an instrumental section after the bridge for a break from vocals
ends with a final chorus and a strong outro to wrap up the song neatly

struct_suggs.name: The Unconventional Flow
attrs: has a unique structure that puts the first prechorus before the first verse
includes a bridge for a change in mood and pace
utilizes an instrumental section after the bridge for added interest
ends with a final chorus and a powerful outro for a strong finish

struct_suggs.name: The Unexpected Turn
attrs: has a unique structure with the bridge before the second verse
includes an instrumental section after the bridge for added variation
utilizes a final chorus and a strong outro to end the song on a high note
maintains a strong structure and flow despite a non-traditional arrangement

struct_suggs.name: The Building Blocks
attrs: has a catchy intro that immediately grabs the listener's attention
includes a bridge before the second verse for a change in pace
has multiple prechorus and chorus repetitions, making it suitable for a longer song
ends with a final chorus and a strong outro for a complete and satisfying ending

struct_suggs.name: The Ladder to Success
attrs: has a unique structure with the bridge before the first chorus
includes a prechorus after the bridge for added build up to the final chorus
utilizes a double chorus after the second verse for a bigger impact
ends with a powerful final chorus and a strong outro for a memorable ending

struct_suggs.name: The Progressive Path
attrs: has a traditional intro and verse-chorus structure
includes an instrumental section after the chorus for added interest
has a distinct build up to the final chorus in the outro
maintains a strong structure and flow throughout the song.

Intro:
do you remember seeing the beatles live?
if so, do you still feel included in this vibe?

Verse 1:
all the lies they tell, got me stressed
but i ain't lettin' it get me, i'm still blessed
gems drop from my mouth, every word a diamond
oh oh no, they can't deny 'em.
said my name one time, now it's stuck in your head,
like a howling wolf, can't escape, i won't be led.
they move quicker, tryna get away from the truth
you throw em, but they can still see the lies from a mile.

Pre-Chorus 1:
feeling lit on this molly, i'll take it as it comes,
gotta get those eggs, mama needs some scrambled for brunch,

Chorus 1:
you have my word, you have my loyalty,
trust in me, i'll be your rock solid continuity.
she been playing me, like i'm some kind of game,
but i ain't lettin' her bring me down, i ain't chasin' no fame,

Verse 2:
if you're not genuine, then get out of my sight,
we're gonna dance till the morning light.
or destroy me with a barely audible whisper
who measures love in pain, only ends up a quitter.
ain't no time for drama, we go winnin',
if you ain't smoking bud, you can't come to our spirit circle for real, that's like tomorrow, or maybe that soon.
i can't keep my mind off that booty, it's a trap,
and all this lean got me moving like a sloth in a nap.

Pre-Chorus 2:
when the shots ring out, it's time to duck,
'cause we shootin' from all angles, nothin' sweet like barry manilow's love.

Chorus 2:
my mind on mars, my feet still on earth,
now i had to come through, show them what i'm worth.
i come at you from all sides, got you on the edge,
had it in my yard, now i'm setting the whole stage.

Bridge:
please let me in, wanna make you holler,
fuck on your mama, while i stir the crockpot, hotter and hotter.
i never needed anyone like i need you now
change your shirt, let's hit the town, we'll take the vow.

Outro:
if my song ever gets played, i'll take it as a sign,
my mind's on mars and i'm riding that rolls, feeling so fine.

Instrumental:
i never needed anyone like i need you now
but you still got me feeling like a bearcat, how?

Intro:
lord knows we just tryna live righteous, roll this backwood and contemplate god,
these are the things that keep me moving when life gets hard.

Verse 1:
we'll hit the dance floor, shake off all the pain,
get sleazy, no heartache can break us, we'll remain.
and it still feels good, despite the pain,
if only then i could go back and change.
not just your average rap niggas,
she say she love me, feeling like machel montano, vibin' with no limit.
you throw 'em, but we all make mistakes,
ain't no need to dwell on the breaks.

Pre-Chorus 1:
freefalling through life, living on the edge
although we're not the same, we're like a synonym, we're on the same page

Chorus 1:
on the 45th episode, you know we got that coke,
but your heart is finally filled, no more broke.
i go where i skeet, leaving my mark behind,
never been a mark, i stand tall and shine.

Verse 2:
elevators take me high, you are so adored,
but deep down i know i'm just running from my demons, that's the real score.
love is as welcome as a stranger in the streets,
in the meantime, it's all about the hustle, can't miss a beat.
and bag em up, gotta keep my cool
even though i'm getting heated, gotta play it as a rule.
now i had to come through, time to let loose,
hit the club, get sleazy, party like there's no use.

Pre-Chorus 2:
got my bags packed, i'm ready to fly,
embracing the unknown, i'm not afraid to try.

Chorus 2:
got that white powder on deck, don't play it coy,
and get rid of that old outfit, go change your clothes, boy.
you throw them words, try to knock me off my game,
but love ain't about hurting, it's not a deadly aim.

Bridge:
all the time, i'm grindin', no stop
keepin' my brother close, he's my rock
diamonds on my neck, bling bling
but my love for my fam, that's the real thing.

Outro:
i'll brush off the hurt and skip the game,
won't get trapped in their bullshit and shame.

Instrumental:
you know we got that white powder, that blow, that yayo
i been on the prowl, howling at the moon like a stray dog, hot and low.
